        <updateDate>2019-04-23T20:51:44Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Contractor Accountability and Workplace Safety Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires contracting officers of the Department of Defense (DOD), before awarding or renewing a contract for the procurement of property or services, including construction, valued over $1 million, to consider any identified violations of the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970 (OSHA) or equivalent state laws by the offeror and any subcontractors. </p> <p>The bill requires DOD to: (1) establish policies and practices with respect to responsibility determinations for contractors, and (2) protect the rights of contractors to protest bids and appeal actions taken under this bill.</p> <p>The Government Accountability Office must report on the health and safety records of DOD contractors.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
